## Backup Scope

This document provides a consolidated reference for backup scope, exclusion lists, and approved exceptions across the backup infrastructure. It identifies workloads protected by backup, items intentionally excluded from backup protection, and approved exception controls such as legal hold and backup image retention extensions.

| Category                        | Backup Position                                                          |
| ------------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------ |
| Physical Servers                | In scope where server-level recovery is required                         |
| Virtual Servers                 | In scope where hosted on supported platforms such as Hyper-V and Nutanix |
| Branch Hyper-V Hosts / Clusters | Limited scope; only approved file and print servers are backed up        |
| Oracle Databases                | In scope where database-level backup is required and onboarded           |
| SQL Databases                   | In scope where database-level backup is required and onboarded           |
| NAS / File Shares               | In scope only where formally onboarded for backup protection             |

